вҡЎ 4. The Multi-Tiered Computer Vision Pipeline

Here is how the complete Computer Vision Pipeline executes in PageWatch.tech when comparing two snapshots:

вҖў
Step 1: Structural Hash Check (Edge) вҖ” Instant HTML AST check. If identical, abort early (Cost = 0ms).

вҖў
Step 2: Global SSIM Map Generation вҖ” Compute sliding window SSIM map over viewport PNGs.

вҖў
Step 3: ORB Layout Alignment вҖ” If SSIM drops in localized regions, run ORB feature matching to detect elastic page layout shifts.

вҖў
Step 4: Neural Semantic Filtering (ONNX) вҖ” For remaining low-SSIM visual patches, pass tensors through the ONNX ResNet-18 embedding model to distinguish cosmetic noise from genuine content changes.

вҖў
Step 5: Alert Overlay Generation вҖ” Highlight only verified, high-confidence semantic changes in bright red.

рҹҸҒ Conclusion

Combining classical SSIM algorithms, ORB rigid feature alignment, and Siamese Neural Networks allowed us to eliminate over 99% of false-positive visual alerts while keeping monitoring instant and reliable.

If you are interested in trying out an intelligent, noise-free website change monitoring tool, check out PageWatch.tech!

